As an AI language model, I can provide you with guidance and code snippets for creating a simple Android game using Java. However, I cannot create a full game exclusively in this format. I suggest you start by getting familiar with Android development using Android Studio. Below is an example of a simple number-guessing game in Java for Android.

First, create a new Android Studio project. Choose an Empty Activity template and give a name to your project.

Then, in `activity_main.xml` layout file, add the necessary elements for the game:

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context=".MainActivity">

    <TextView
        android:id="@+id/tv_game_title"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Guess the Number"
        android:textSize="24sp"
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf="@id/tv_game_instruction"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintTop_toTopOf="parent" />

    <TextView
        android:id="@+id/tv_game_instruction"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Enter a number between 1 and 100:"
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf="@id/et_guess"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf="@id/tv_game_title" />

    <EditText
        android:id="@+id/et_guess"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:ems="10"
        android:inputType="number"
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf="@id/btn_submit"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf="@id/tv_game_instruction" />

    <Button
        android:id="@+id/btn_submit"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:text="Submit"
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf="@id/tv_game_result"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf="@id/et_guess" />

    <TextView
        android:id="@+id/tv_game_result"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintHorizontal_bias="0.478"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf="@id/btn_submit" />

</androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>
```

Next, in `MainActivity.java`, implement the game logic:

```java
package com.example.guessthenumber;

import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;
import android.os.Bundle;
import android.view.View;
import android.widget.Button;
import android.widget.EditText;
import android.widget.TextView;
import java.util.Random;

public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {

    private EditText etGuess;
    private TextView tvGameResult;
    private int randomNumber;

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);

        etGuess = findViewById(R.id.et_guess);
        tvGameResult = findViewById(R.id.tv_game_result);
        Button btnSubmit = findViewById(R.id.btn_submit);

        generateRandomNumber();

        btnSubmit.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                int guessedNumber = Integer.parseInt(etGuess.getText().toString());
                checkGuess(guessedNumber);
            }
        });
    }

    private void generateRandomNumber() {
        Random random = new Random();
        randomNumber = random.nextInt(100) + 1;
    }

    private void checkGuess(int guessedNumber) {
        if (guessedNumber > randomNumber) {
            tvGameResult.setText(R.string.result_too_high);
        } else if (guessedNumber < randomNumber) {
            tvGameResult.setText(R.string.result_too_low);
        } else {
            tvGameResult.setText(R.string.result_correct_guess);
            generateRandomNumber();
        }
    }
}
```

This is a basic example of a number-guessing game for Android. You can further customize the game by modifying the layout and adding features to enhance the gameplay experience.
